column4: <content>Ad [Addendum] 19. Witt Library. P.B.II. Woman taken in Adultery (copy after A.S. picture): 1) A. Schloss Collection, signed P. BRVEGHEL, Bois 27 x 37 cm, Vente Ter Bruggen, Anvers, 17 Oct. 1854, coll. Cloix à Paris. In Colours?[sic]; 2) Mentioned a Mount of II: Replica in Johnson Coll., Philadelphia 323; 3) Decock Sale, Charpentier Paris, 12 May 1948, N° 35, Bois 25 x 35 cm, signed left bottom without date. In colour; [verso] 4) Sale Giroux, Brussels, 22.II.1952, N° 639, Bois, 24 x 34. Looks like grisaille.</content>
<object.title>Christ and the Woman Taken in Adultery</object.title>
